Collita okanoi is a moth of the  family Erebidae. It is found on the southern Kuriles (Kunashir, Shikotan) and in Japan (Hokkaido, Honshu, Kyushu).The wingspan is 28â€“32 mm. The ground colour of the wings is brown-grey. The forewing costal streak is yellow and wider in the basal half. The hindwings are coloured evenly and are paler than the forewings.